Minister Nomvula Mokonyane said there's a possibility the province will be declared a disaster area, which could mean extra funding from government. CAPE TOWN - Water and Sanitation Minister Nomvula Mokonyane has been meeting with Western Cape government officials to discuss their findings regarding the ongoing drought.National Disaster Management officials have been assessing the province and are providing feedback to the minister.Mokonyane met with provincial Local Government, Environment and Development Planning MEC Anton Bredell last week about the water crisis.Mokonyane said there's a possibility that the province will be declared a disaster area, which could mean extra funding from national government for larger water infrastructure projects in the province.Department of Water and Sanitation spokesperson Mlimandlela Ndamase says: The minister is meeting with the officials to consider some of the points that emanated from their work from last week. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)